<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="horror-n">horror <strong><em>n</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'hɒrə(r)/    美 /'hɔːrər/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-u">1.★ <strong>[U] 恐怖；惊恐：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>a horror movie
恐怖片</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She turned away <strong>in horror</strong> at the sight of so much blood.
看到这么多血，她吓得转过身去。</p></div>

<h4 id="2-c">2.★ <strong>[C] [常用复数] 使人感到恐怖的东西：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The horrors of war are beyond description.
战争的恐怖难以言表。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="to-sbs-horror-to-the-horror-of-sb">to sb's horror / to the horror of sb</h3>
<p>1.<strong>使某人感到惊恐的是：</strong>  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>To my horror, a child fell from the roof.
令我感到惊恐的是，有个孩子从房顶上掉了下来。</p></div></div>